14/08/2003
MARMARIS, Turkey -- A joint naval military exercise involving Turkish, Israeli and US forces began Wednesday (13 August) in international waters in the eastern Mediterranean. 
According to a Turkish press release, the aim of the exercise is to try out new search and rescue procedures and to ensure co-ordination between naval and air forces in such operations. 
A number of Egyptian, Israeli, US and Jordanian military officials are monitoring the exercise. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 13/08/03)
